#X text 71 19 You can compare with the earlier version of this. Note we have a couple of detuned oscillators on both voices. To the left they are detuned by plus and minus 5 cents \, so it's a 10 cents detuning. To the right we have +10 and -10 cents (20 cents total). There's no filter modulation at all in here \, which can be common in subtractive synths. You can bypass the filter by clicking on the toggle to see how it affects the sound. Anyway \, they are rythmic bass sections \, so nothing more natural than filtering them with a lowpass., f 85;
