#X text 485 595 The same patch with MERDA modules., f 19;
#X text 481 649 Next examples will include proper modulations., f 26;
#X text 449 140 Actually \, many subtractive synths will actually have more than one oscillator and adding them (aka wave stacking) is even more important in the sound design process. So don't let commonly applied terminology deceive you., f 36;
#X text 449 244 Hence \, subtractive synths are better described as modular systems where you can combine oscillators \, filters and modulate them with LFOs \, envelopes and such \, because \, yes \, filter modulation is not the only modulating possibility usually. Hence \, arguably \, subtractive synthesis could be treated under the 'Modulation.Synthesis' part that comes next in this tutorial. And also \, the techniques we'll see later in that section can also include modulation of filter that we know as "subtractive synthesis"., f 38;
#X text 449 448 For now we'll expand on an earlier wave stacking example and increment on the sound design principles. Instead of a single oscillator going through an envelope generator \, we combine two detuned oscillators and filter them., f 38;
